data.name: The St. Paul Grill

photo.caption: Ahi Tuna Charlie with Caesar Salad 07-17-17

data.description: Open since 1990 and brimming with energy and nostalgia, The St. Paul Grill is a destination unto itself. Located in the historic Saint Paul Hotel and overlooking Rice Park, the iconic restaurant is known for its refined style, attentive service, and exceptional cuisine. Our culinary team prepares American steakhouse classics with unparalleled quality and attention-to-detail. Our bar program boasts an impressive selection of rare spirits, an award-winning wine list, and a collection of classic cocktails. Our team of passionate bartenders, servers, and hospitality professionals are intuitive, enthusiastic, and always authentically themselves.
data.address: 350 N Market Street, Saint Paul, MN 55102-1430

data.name: Downtowner Woodfire Grill
data.description: "simply beyond the ordinary""****" - Kathie Jenkins - Saint Paul Pioneer PressDowntowner Woodfire Grill specializes in Persian fire roasted meats, grilled steaks and chops, and gourmet wood-fired pizzas.  The atmosphere is warm & lively offering 2 fireplaces, a full bar with 3 fountains and live jazz.  The restaurant offers free parking with convenience to both the Xcel Energy Center & Ordway Theater.  Downtowner Woodfire Grill also provides a full menu for breakfast & lunch, and a children's menu.  This cozy restaurant serves a great plate as well as provides an experience to savor.

data.name: Brasa Rotisserie
data.description: Brasa serves comfort food inspired by the traditions of Creole cooking. Our menu is a celebration of new and old world ingredients, representing native influences and many many styles of cooking. We supply our kitchen with locally sourced products, free range and pasture raised meats, eggs, and dairy. We also feature organic ingredients, fair trade coffee & tea.
